montpelier vt bureau of the associated press has been named ap 
correspondent in stamford 
the appointment was announced thursday by hartford chief of 
bureau mary anne rhyne 
ms arabas 27 joined the ap in montpelier in 1986 after working 
as a reporter for the standard times of new bedford mass 
she is a native of mount kisco ny and a graduate of the 
university of new hampshire 
in stamford she succeeds brent laymon who has been named aps 
news editor in hartford 
