national security officials in washington in 198385 to dispute 
optimistic projections by physicist edward teller about the xray 
laser weapon being developed there 
the xray laser uses the energy of a nuclear explosion in space 
to destroy enemy rocket boosters 
separately the general accounting office the investigative arm 
of congress is looking into allegations of thefts of government 
property at the lab that investigation was launched last year after 
dingells panel was told in a public hearing that some lab employees 
had sold computers and other government assets for drug money 
the lab in 1986 launched its own investigation of drug 
trafficking by employees after a number of workers became involved 
in drugrelated incidents and arrests 
last month the lab was embarrassed when small amounts of cocaine 
and other drugs were stolen from a locked safe the narcotics were 
being used to train a drugsniffing dog that had been brought onto 
the site to fight a drug problem 
