negotiating process as it were in the medical field 
weve moved away from an era when the doctor made all the 
decisions and sometimes didnt tell the patient everything 
questions still exist however when that person has no way to 
communicate his or her wants 
ms putilo said these kinds of lifeanddeath ethical decisions 
are difficult for judges doctors patients families involved and 
sometimes the best decision is the one that hurts everybody the 
least 
there is not right and wrong she explained there are 
several rights and wrongs a person just has to choose the most of 
the right and the least of the wrong 
