on friday st joseph county quit 
collaborating with cupid 
district court administrator david recher said he stopped 
performing 10 nofrills civil marriages because of an overburdened 
and underfunded court 
recher said he usually performs about 100 weddings a year 
prompting weary court personnel to refer to the ceremonies as the 
countys 1000ayear headache 
personnel shortages and an increasing criminal caseload have 
forced more than one lovestruck couple to cool their ardor on 
folding chairs in the courts lobby while recher attended to 
criminal cases 
from now on recher said couples will have to take their rings 
and rice to neighboring counties 
st joseph county magistrates have been performing ceremonies for 
about 20 years although state law does not require the service 
recher said his ceremonies are usually brief with the paperwork 
taking more time than the i dos 
if theyre in a really big rush i just ask them if they accept 
each other without any coercion or constraint and pronounce them 
married recher said 
ive had guys come in to get married in dirty oily tshirts 
right from work and get irritated if it takes too long because they 
want to get back to work 
the magistrate said he might resume the rites if voters on 
tuesday approve a tax increase that leads to reinstatement of a 
second fulltime magistrate 
