a rubber duck race has turned into a 
floating fundraiser because the original idea ran afoul of state 
gambling laws 
the organizers delta gamma lincoln alumnae had planned for 
people to pay to sponsor rubber ducks and for prizes to be awarded 
to the sponsors of the first fake fowls to cross the finish line 
but deputy tax commissioner roger hirsch said the star city duck 
dash set for sept 24 would have violated state law on raffles and 
lotteries 
you can race all the ducks you want but you cant gamble on 
the outcome hirsch said 
the only races nebraskans can gamble on legally are run by horses 
at licensed race tracks he said 
so hirsch and representatives of the alumnae agreed to a new 
approach to the race of 4000 rubber ducks in salt creek each duck 
will wear a band with the name and serial number of the sponsoring 
organization and a ticket number people will pay 5 to sponsor a 
duck 
after the race is concluded hirsch said some lucky person is 
going to wade into salt creek and draw the lucky duck 
we will consider the widdle band around the widdle neck of the 
widdle duck to be a ticket hirsch said 
