somalia the dispute centered on conflicting claims to the ogaden 
region of ethiopia 
the cuban action soured what had been a promising start toward a 
more normal relationship between the united states and cuba 
the two countries opened diplomatic missions in each others 
capital in september 1977 but with the dispatch of the troops to 
ethiopia progress toward improved relations was halted 
