after herding 2700 bawling longhorns across the prairie 
the procession with 100 drovers tending the herd and 200 
covered wagons and 3000 dusty riders trailing behind headed 
toward its final camp friday many participants in the sixday 
60mile drive believed they were making history as part of the 
wests last great cattle drive 
id hoped to see a few more cows and not so many people said 
