of 1048 said exchange economist vic demayo in 1983 a metric ton 
of cocoa sold for 2800 he said 
the ivory coast the worlds biggest producer whose international 
debts total more than 14 billion is spearheading efforts to revive 
the cocoa organization cocoa is the source of 30 percent of the 
foreign exchange earnings of ivory coast and is an even more 
important earner for ghana 
